{"id":682932581,"lang":"javascript","lang_name":"JavaScript","time":"1 year, 2 months","timestamp":1650303227,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"81 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/682932581/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"String to Integer (atoi)","memory":"44.6 MB","code":"/**\n * @param {string} s\n * @return {number}\n */\n\nvar myAtoi = function(input) {\n    let sign = 1; \n    let result = 0;\n    let index = 0;\n    let n = input.length;\n    \n    let INT_MAX = Math.pow(2,31) - 1;\n    let INT_MIN = -Math.pow(2, 31);\n        \n    // Discard all spaces from the beginning of the input string.\n    while (index < n && input[index] == ' ') { \n        index++; \n    }\n\n    // sign = +1, if it's positive number, otherwise sign = -1. \n    if (index < n && input[index] == '+') {\n        sign = 1;\n        index++;\n    } else if (index < n && input[index] == '-') {\n        sign = -1;\n        index++;\n    }\n\n    // Traverse next digits of input and stop if it is not a digit. \n    // End of string is also non-digit character.\n    while (index < n && input[index] >= '0' && input[index] <= '9') {\n        let digit = input[index] - '0';\n\n        // Check overflow and underflow conditions. \n        if ((result > Math.floor(INT_MAX / 10)) || \n            (result == Math.floor(INT_MAX / 10) && digit > INT_MAX % 10)) {     \n            // If integer overflowed return 2^31-1, otherwise if underflowed return -2^31.    \n            return sign == 1 ? INT_MAX : INT_MIN;\n        }\n\n        // Append current digit to the result.\n        result = 10 * result + digit;\n        index++;\n    }\n\n    // We have formed a valid number without any overflow/underflow.\n    // Return it after multiplying it with its sign.\n    return sign * result;\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"string-to-integer-atoi","has_notes":false}
